# Commit Steps
Create Workspace root folder
Open git bash in the workspace root folder

$ mkdir Project_Name
$ cd Project_Name
$ git init
$ git config --global user.name "Your name here"
$ git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"
$ git remote add origin "URL ofthe git repository"
$ git pull origin master
$ echo "node-modules/" > .gitignore

copy your files you want to commit, or do the changes then :
$ git add .
$ git commit -m "first commit"
$ git push -u origin master

To reset local commit (It will remove uncommited changes and merge with the origin provided ) be careful.
$ git reset --hard origin/master or $ git reset --hard 

To reset logged-in account
$ git credential-manager delete https://github.com
